{"HARNESS":[{"def":"Originally, the complete dress, especially in a military sense, of a man or a horse; hence, in general, armor.","pos":""},{"def":"The equipment of a draught or carriage horse, for drawing a wagon, coach, chaise, etc.","pos":""}],"HARNESS CASK":[{"def":"A tub lashed to a vessel's deck and containing salted provisions for daily use; -- called also harness tub.","pos":""}],"HARNESSER":[{"def":"One who harnesses.","pos":""}]}